cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on self-supervised visual representation learning for domain adaptation in computer vision tasks, specifically object recognition and semantic segmentation of urban scenes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes different learning strategies and complementary techniques to improve domain adaptation effectiveness, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use case of urban scenes suggests a possible sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics and Control) as well. Finally, the paper also discusses the relevant setting of training models using synthetic images and adapting them to real-world images, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
